subSubSection.paragraph:
Differs from the other members of the tribe Chromosereae by its larger and more robust basidiomata, concolorous yellow pileus, lamellae and the subsurface of stipe, usually furcate and interveined lamellae and lamellulae, white fibrillose stipe surface, long basidia (up to 80 
μm
), ratio of basidia to basidiospore length over 5 and even up to 8.
